22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Joe%20Biden%3A%20President%20As%20A%20Prisoner%20Of%20Wars%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fj8vcnhtg_biden_625x300_21_October_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20start%20of%20the%20countdown%20to%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%20Biden's%20Presidency%2C%20it%20may%20seem%20early%20to%20assess%20the%20global%20legacy%20of%20his%20presidency.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20relentless%20momentum%20of%20his%20presidency%20is%20going%20to%20be%20unsparing%20till%20January%2020%2C%202025.%20Yet%2C%20he%20has%20already%20been%20a%20lame-duck%20president%20for%20the%20past%20quarter%20after%20opting%20out%20of%20the%20re-run%2C%20and%20a%20vote%20on%20his%20successor%20has%20been%20scheduled%20for%20a%20fortnight.%20Today%20being%20exactly%20the%20midway%20point%20between%20his%20opt-out%20and%20eventual%20exit%2C%20the%20time%20is%20apt%20to%20assess%20the%20foreign%20policy%20of%20his%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInherited%20Mess%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Joe%20Biden%20became%20the%2046th%20American%20President%20at%2078%2C%20he%20brought%20to%20the%20job%20nearly%20half%20a%20century%20of%20political%20experience%2C%20including%20two%20stints%20as%20the%20Vice-President.%20The%20baggage%20made%20him%20more%20phlegmatic%20and%20deliberative%2C%20but%20also%20a%20hostage%20to%20his%20experience%20and%20past%20interpersonal%20interactions.%20He%20found%20the%20United%20States%20in%20an%20unusual%20condition%3A%20a%20pandemic%20had%20debilitated%20its%20society%20and%20economy.%20He%20also%20inherited%20a%20fractious%20legacy%20of%20his%20predecessor's%20whimsical%20foreign%20policy%20that%20had%20confounded%20allies%20and%20opponents%20alike.%20The%20diplomatic%20faux%20pas%20of%20Trump's%20presidency%20sent%20mixed%20signals%20to%20longstanding%20friends%20like%20Mexico%2C%20NATO%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Israel.%20Its%20'blow%20hot%2C%20blow%20cold'%20style%20either%20confused%20or%20emboldened%20opponents%20such%20as%20the%20Afghan%20Taleban%2C%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20North%20Korea%20and%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20his%20credit%2C%20President%20Biden%20tried%20to%20stabilise%20the%20US%20foreign%20policy%20by%20making%20it%20more%20rational%20and%20predictable.%20He%20was%20able%20to%20re-establish%20normalcy%20within%20NATO%2C%20revive%20Pivot%20Asia%20and%20rejoin%20the%20multilateral%20mainstream.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20opted%20for%20continuity%20on%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20geo-economic%20tensions%20with%20China%20and%20Iran%20nuclear%20imbroglio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Ideals%20That%20Defined%20Biden%20Years%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Biden's%20foreign%20policy%20is%20not%20without%20its%20idiosyncrasies.%20It%20has%20ideological%20underpinnings%20in%20somewhat%20outdated%20mid-20th-century%20ideals%20of%20liberal%20internationalism%2C%20American%20exceptionalism%20(without%20his%20predecessor's%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%20dictum)%2C%20and%20pragmatism.%20His%20reluctance%20for%20military%20engagements%20abroad%20bordered%20on%20isolationism.%20These%20proclivities%20often%20impelled%20in%20unintended%20directions%2C%20limiting%20their%20policy%20impact.%20For%20instance%2C%20his%20initial%20public%20reluctance%20to%20engage%20the%20leaderships%20in%20Israel%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Turkey%20and%20the%20UAE%20narrowed%20his%20diplomatic%20manoeuvrability%2C%20created%20bilateral%20tensions%20and%20raised%20subsequent%20opportunity%20costs.%20These%20foibles%20allowed%20China%20and%20Russia%20to%20make%20inroads%20with%20these%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%209%2F11%2C%20tenures%20of%20successive%20US%20Presidents%20have%20been%20preoccupied%20with%20%26quot%3Bforever%20wars%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20President%20Biden%20was%20no%20exception.%20Although%20he%20was%20cautious%20to%20a%20fault%20about%20foreign%20military%20engagements%2C%20his%20term%20was%20dented%20by%20conflicts%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%20As%20these%20three%20military%20engagements%20have%20cast%20a%20long%20and%20dark%20shadow%20on%20his%20presidential%20legacy%2C%20their%20granular%20study%20is%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Chaotic%20Withdrawal%20From%20Afghanistan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20invaded%20Afghanistan%20in%20the%20immediate%20aftermath%20of%209%2F11%2C%20overthrowing%20the%20Taleban%20regime%2C%20evicting%20al-Qaeda%20and%20installing%20a%20friendly%20government.%20However%2C%20with%20Pakistani%20duplicity%2C%20Taleban%20was%20able%20to%20wage%20an%20effective%20insurgency%20against%20the%20US%20forces%2C%20tiring%20Washington%20of%20its%20longest%20(20%20years)%20and%20most%20expensive%20(%242.3%20trillion)%20foreign%20military%20engagement.%20After%20protracted%20talks%20in%20Doha%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20signed%20a%20deal%20in%20February%202020%20providing%20for%20a%20progressive%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20US%20and%20NATO%20troops%20from%20Afghanistan%20by%20May%2031%202021%2C%20against%20Taleban's%20solemn%20promise%20to%20have%20an%20interim%20national%20government%20and%20non-use%20of%20Afghan%20territory%20for%20al-Qaeda%20or%20other%20terrorists.%20Thus%2C%20when%20Biden's%20Presidency%20began%20in%20January%202021%2C%20there%20were%20nearly%202%2C500%20US%20troops%20in%20Afghanistan%20helping%20President%20Ashraf%20Ghani's%20fairly%20well-equipped%20army.%20Against%20the%20advice%20of%20its%20working%20group%2C%20which%20warned%20that%20an%20early%20total%20withdrawal%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20Taleban%20takeover%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20decided%20exactly%20the%20opposite%3A%20to%20pull%20out%20all%20the%20troops%20by%20the%20end%20of%20July%202021.%20This%20decision%20demoralised%20the%20Afghan%20army%2C%20emboldened%20Taleban%20and%20caused%20a%20chaotic%20exodus.%20President%20Ghani%20escaped%20the%20country%20heralding%20a%20Taleban%20takeover%20of%20the%20country%20on%20August%2015%2C%202021.%20While%20President%20Biden%20sought%20to%20justify%20the%20withdrawal%2C%20the%20fact%20remains%20that%20after%20the%20deaths%20of%206%2C337%20Americans%20and%201%2C144%20allied%20troops%2C%20the%20US%20handed%20the%20country%20back%20to%20Taleban%20with%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20military%20hardware%20as%20a%20parting%20gift!%20After%20the%201975%20Saigon%20airlift%2C%20this%20was%20the%20most%20evocative%20and%20humiliating%20withdrawal%20by%20the%20global%20superpower%20against%20a%20ragtag%20army%20of%20Islamic%20zealots.%20This%20avoidable%20self-goal%20also%20sent%20a%20lasting%20message%20of%20the%20unreliability%20of%20the%20American%20staying%20power%20when%20faced%20with%20a%20stubborn%20enemy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Israel-Gaza%20War%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20benefit%20of%20hindsight%2C%20the%20ongoing%20Middle%20East%20crisis%20was%20apparently%20triggered%20by%20the%20need%20to%20counter%20the%20perceived%20attempt%20to%20short-shrift%20the%20Palestinian%20Cause%20by%20the%20US%20by%20corralling%20the%20moderate%20Arabs%20to%20normalise%20relations%20with%20Israel.%20While%20the%20means%20and%20methods%20used%20by%20Hamas%20on%20October%207%20%26quot%3BOperation%20Toofan%20Al-Aqsa%26quot%3B%20were%20abominable%20and%20unjustifiable%2C%20the%20perpetrators%20sought%20to%20deliver%20a%20disruptive%20shock%20to%20prevent%20the%20Palestinian%20Cause%20from%20being%20buried%20under%20the%20incipient%20structure%20of%20the%20Abraham%20Accords.%20While%20the%20Trump%20administration%20blessed%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20between%20Israel%20and%20four%20Arab%20countries%2C%20Biden's%20foreign%20policy%20sought%20to%20extend%20it%20further%20by%20bringing%20Saudi%20Arabia%20into%20the%20game%20and%20pushing%20for%20the%20India-Middle%20East-Europe%20Economic%20Corridor.%20It%20led%20to%20the%20October%207%20mayhem%20as%20the%20panic%20reaction.%20In%20retrospect%2C%20the%20unfolding%20Arab-Israel%20%3Cem%3Eentente%20cordiale%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20too%20much%20to%20continence%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Brejectionist%26quot%3B%20Arab-Islamic%20regimes%20and%20non-state%20actors.%20President%20Biden's%20foreign%20policy%20minders%20failed%20to%20anticipate%20the%20political%20anticyclone%20gathering%20near%20the%20horizon%20leading%20to%20the%20biggest%20bloodletting%20the%20region%20has%20seen%20for%20two%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20year%20on%2C%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20wider%20regional%20war%20is%20still%20hanging%20over%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Biden%20administration's%20inconsistent%20mixed%20messaging%20in%20supporting%20Israel's%20war%20while%20mouthing%20platitudes%20about%20the%20ceasefire%20and%20humanitarian%20relief%20is%20partly%20to%20be%20blamed%20for%20the%20death%20and%20destruction.%20Once%20again%2C%20glitzy%20military%20successes%20in%20the%20short%20term%20are%20glossing%20over%20the%20need%20for%20a%20two-state%20political%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrevaricating%20In%20Ukraine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilar%20patterns%20of%20demurral%20and%20ambiguity%20have%20been%20evident%20in%20Biden's%20foreign%20policy%20towards%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict%20that%20began%20in%20February%202022.%20Even%20before%20the%20conflict%20began%2C%20President%20Biden%20seemed%20reluctant%20to%20lay%20down%20clear%20redlines%20for%20Russia.%20There%20was%20considerable%20jostling%20over%20the%20crucial%20decision%20about%20Ukraine%20joining%20NATO%20-%20a%20key%20Russian%20redline.%20The%20quantum%20and%20quality%20of%20military%20assistance%20to%20Ukraine%20and%20conditions%20on%20its%20offensive%20usage%20against%20targets%20deep%20inside%20Russia%20were%20often%20too%20little%2C%20too%20late.%20Similarly%2C%20though%20Biden%20imposed%20hundreds%20of%20economic%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%2C%20these%20were%20largely%20ineffective%20and%20Moscow%20was%20able%20to%20circumvent%20them%20with%20the%20help%20of%20its%20friends%20such%20as%20China.%20Biden's%20policy%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%20seems%20to%20lack%20firmness%2C%20clarity%20and%20consistency%20being%20constantly%20buffeted%20by%20pressures%20from%20Congress%2C%20the%20domestic%20military-industrial%20complex%20and%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20state%26quot%3B%2C%20NATO%20allies%2C%20Ukrainian%20desperation%20and%20manipulation%2C%20as%20well%20as%20an%20overarching%20concern%20to%20avoid%20a%20direct%20conflict%20between%20NATO%20and%20Russia.%20These%20factors%20resulted%20in%20constant%20prevarication%2C%20causing%20the%20American%20assistance%20of%20over%20%24176%20billion%20(larger%20than%20Ukraine's%20GDP)%20to%20yield%20a%20sub-optimal%20impact%20on%20the%20complex%20and%20evolving%20geo-strategic%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20kind%20to%20President%20Biden's%20legacy%2C%20one%20can%20concede%20that%20it%20did%20not%20cause%20any%20of%20these%20three%20conflicts%20but%20allowed%20his%20administration%20to%20be%20sucked%20into%20them.%20However%2C%20as%20Yogi%20Berra%20would%20have%20put%20it%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bpath%20to%20hell%20is%20often%20paved%20with%20inconsistent%20intentions%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Mahesh%20Sachdev%20is%20a%20former%20Indian%20Ambassador.%20He%20currently%20heads%20Eco-Diplomacy%20and%20Strategies%2C%20a%20Delhi-based%20consultancy)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729490340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fo0jvqcu8_biden_625x300_21_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fus-president-joe-bi