ollar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Florida%20couple%20is%20facing%20charges%20of%20stealing%20properties%20through%20a%20simple%20scam%20that%20costs%20less%20than%20a%20dollar%20to%20execute.%20Victor%20Rodriguez%2C%2050%2C%20and%20his%20wife%20Michelle%20Cherry%2C%2033%2C%20allegedly%20forged%20%E2%80%9Cquitclaim%20deeds%E2%80%9D%20to%20illegally%20transfer%20ownership%20of%20homes%2C%20including%20a%20property%20owned%20by%20Rodriguez's%20ex-father-in-law%2C%20in%20Tampa%20and%20Miami-Dade%20County%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fox13news.com%2Fnews%2Fproperty-fraud-investigation-extends-from-bay-area-south-florida-court-documents%C2%A0%5C%22%3EFox%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECaroline%20Sauer%2C%20Rodriguez's%20ex-wife%2C%20discovered%20the%20scam%20when%20she%20found%20that%20her%20father's%20properties%20had%20changed%20ownership%20through%20quitclaim%20deeds.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20questioned%2C%20how%20did%20this%20happen%3F%E2%80%9D%20Ms%20Sauer%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWho%20forges%20a%20deceased%20person's%20signature%3F%20Who%20does%20that%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20authorities%2C%20the%20scam%20involved%20forging%20signatures%20on%20quitclaim%20deeds%20%E2%80%93%20a%20legal%20document%20that%20transfers%20property%20ownership%20with%20the%20owner's%20consent.%20These%20documents%2C%20however%2C%20can%20be%20easily%20manipulated.%20Fraudsters%20only%20need%20a%20notary%20and%20two%20signatures%20to%20process%20the%20transaction%2C%20often%20for%20as%20little%20as%2070%20cents%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERodriguez%20and%20Cherry%20allegedly%20used%20the%20same%20scam%20on%20another%20Tampa%20property%20belonging%20to%20Larry%20and%20Dreama%20Bilby.%20The%20Bilbys%20were%20stunned%20when%20they%20learned%20in%20February%20that%20someone%20forged%20their%20signatures%20and%20transferred%20ownership%20of%20their%20home%2C%20which%20was%20unoccupied%20and%20under%20construction%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3