of%20political%20economy%20at%20Harvard's%20Kennedy%20School%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20while%20some%20employers%20might%20no%20longer%20require%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20for%20certain%20roles%2C%20those%20doing%20the%20hiring%20still%20might%20care%20whether%20an%20applicant%20has%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFirms%20are%20wanting%20credit%20for%20removing%20a%20requirement%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20they're%20changing%20their%20hiring%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeming%20said%20many%20employers%20look%20upon%20a%20worker%20with%20a%20four-year%20degree%20as%20an%20investment%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20can%20be%20molded%20into%20what%20the%20firm%20wants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2269b8e63e-70be-4448-99d6-752bcbe1d346%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHiring%20based%20on%20skills%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Burning%20Glass%20Institute%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20examines%20the%20future%20of%20work%20and%20learning%2C%20and%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20found%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hbs.edu%2Fmanaging-the-future-of-work%2FDocuments%2Fresearch%2FSkills-Based%2520Hiring.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20in%20early%202024%20that%20even%20when%20employers%20hire%20people%20without%20four-year%20degrees%20for%20roles%20that%20once%20required%20them%2C%20it%20doesn't%20occur%20in%20large%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHiring%20for%20skills%20or%20experience%20rather%20than%20for%20formal%20education%20accounted%20for%20just%20one%20in%20700%20hires%20in%202023%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20examined%20more%20than%2011%2C000%20roles%20at%20large%20firms%20and%20compared%20hiring%20at%20least%20a%20year%20before%20and%20after%20the%20employer%20ditched%20a%20degree%20requirement.%20The%20study%20reviewed%20changes%20in%20roles%20from%202014%20to%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReluctance%20by%20some%20employers%20to%20bring%20on%20workers%20without%20four-year%20degrees%20matters%20because%20only%20about%2036%25%20of%20people%2025%20and%20older%20in%20the%20US%20had%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20or%20higher%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Census%20Bureau.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20part%2C%20that's%20because%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-skipping-college-living-paycheck-to-paycheck-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20cost%20of%20tuition%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20a%20major%20barrier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22448d7f69-1fca-482e-a27e-c42712ac78c2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20boost%20for%20employers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20workers%20based%20on%20their%20abilities%20rather%20than%20what's%20on%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20can%20be%20a%20win%20for%20business.%20The%20consulting%20firm%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%2C%20citing%20research%2C%20notes%20that%20hiring%20for%20skills%20is%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fcapabilities%2Fpeople-and-organizational-performance%2Four-insights%2Ftaking-a-skills-based-approach-to-building-the-future-workforce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efive%20times%20more%20predictive%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20of%20how%20someone%20performs%20on%20a%20job%20than%20hiring%20based%20on%20educational%20attainment%20and%20more%20than%20twice%20as%20predictive%20than%20hiring%20based%20on%20a%20person's%20work%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoston%20Consulting%20Group%20research%20found%20that%20those%20hired%20based%20on%20their%20skills%20tend%20to%20get%20promoted%20at%20about%20the%20same%20pace%20as%20traditional%20hires%20yet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bcg.com%2Fpublications%2F2023%2Frise-of-skills-based-hiring%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estay%20with%20an%20employer%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%209%25%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Mona%20Mourshed%2C%20the%20founding%20CEO%20of%20Generation%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20network%20focused%20on%20economic%20mobility%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20while%20many%20notable%20and%20large%20organizations%20support%20skills-first%20hiring%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20vast%20majority%20of%20employers%20are%20not%20there%20yet%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20practice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20Generation%20recently%20completed%20nearly%20100%20interviews%20with%20large%20and%20midsize%20employers%20around%20the%20world%2C%20including%20in%20the%20US%2C%20asking%20what%20goes%20into%20their%20hiring%20decisions.%20Much%20of%20it%2C%20she%20said%2C%20comes%20down%20to%20hiring%20managers%20wanting%20to%20limit%20risk.%20Often%2C%20it's%20easiest%20to%20go%20with%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20that%20looks%20similar%20to%20what%20previous%20hires%20have%20had%2C%20Mourshed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployers%20will%20only%20hire%20a%20different%20profile%20when%20they%20are%20desperate%20for%20talent%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMourshed%20said%20that%20even%20for%20organizations%20that%20might%20be%20open%20to%20looking%20first%20at%20skills%2C%20cuts%20to%20HR%20departments%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20stretched%20some%20recruiting%20teams.%20That%20means%20there%20could%20be%20fewer%20people%20to%20take%20a%20second%20look%20at%20someone%20who%20doesn't%20hold%20the%20typical%20academic%20qualifications%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223055d66a-7df6-45c2-8c68-1871f46e67be%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20'easiest%20and%20laziest%20filter'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Hyams%2C%20CEO%20of%20Indeed%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20for%20many%20jobs%2C%20employers%20simply%20default%20to%20the%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20people%20are%20looking%20for%2C%20because%20it's%20the%20easiest%20and%20laziest%20filter%2C%20is%20a%20four-year%20degree%20from%20a%20'good%20school%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20often%20short-sighted%2C%20Hyams%20said.%20He%20pointed%20to%20the%20plight%20of%20his%20brother-in-law%2C%20whom%20Hyams%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20brilliant%20guy%26quot%3B%20who%20didn't%20finish%20college.%20Instead%2C%20he%20built%20and%20ran%20a%20music%20studio%20before%20becoming%20a%20Salesforce%20administrator%2C%20Hyams%20said.%20Yet%2C%20he%20has%20had%20a%20difficult%20time%20finding%20work%20after%20losing%20his%20job%20about%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20been%20the%20finalist%20for%20five%20different%20positions%20where%20they%20said%2C%20'You're%20actually%20the%20best%20candidate%20we%20interviewed%2C%20but%20we%20require%20a%20four-year%20degree%2C'%26quot%3B%20Hyams%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20dumbest%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20BCG%2C%20there%20are%2070%20million%20workers%20in%20America%20who%20are%20so-called%20STARs%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bcg.com%2Fpublications%2F2023%2Frise-of-skills-based-hiring%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskilled%20through%20alternative%20routes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2238c1ee96-779b-4954-8bf5-e31158131cde%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorkers%20will%20need%20more%20training%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20coming%20years%2C%20many%20workers%20will%20need%20more%2C%20not%20less%2C%20learning%20to%20do%20their%20jobs.%20The%20US%20Department%20of%20Education%20forecasts%20that%20by%202027%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fabout%2Fed-initiatives%2Fraise-bar%2Fraise-the-bar-postsecondary-and-career-pathways%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E70%25%20of%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20require%20schooling%20or%20training%20beyond%20high%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20that%20might%20mean%20a%20four-year%20degree.%20Researchers%20at%20the%20Georgetown%20University%20Center%20on%20Education%20and%20the%20Workforce%20estimate%20that%2042%25%20of%20jobs%20in%202031%20will%20require%20candidates%20to%20have%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcew.georgetown.edu%2Fcew-reports%2Fprojections2031%2F%23resources%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20bachelor's%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%2028%25%20of%20jobs%20will%20need%20someone%20to%20have%20a%20high%20school%20diploma%20or%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBethlam%20Forsa%2C%20CEO%20of%20Savvas%20Learning%20Company%2C%20which%20produces%20instructional%20materials%20for%20kindergarten%20through%20high%20school%20students%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20there's%20often%20a%20gap%20between%20the%20%26quot%3Bjob-ready%26quot%3B%20skills%20students%20possess%20and%20what%20employers%20seek.%20She%20said%20research%20has%20shown%20that%20students%20who%20don't%20want%20to%20attend%20college%20are%20often%20not%20told%20about%20alternative%20paths%20like%20internships%20or%20career%20and%20technical%20education%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20system%20that's%20primarily%20college-bound%2C%26quot%3B%20Forsa%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20employers%20might%20need%20to%20adapt%20their%20evaluation%20methods%20to%20better%20assess%20what%20job%20seekers%20can%20do.%20Employers%20could%2C%20for%20example%2C%20look%20to%20any%20certifications%20an%20applicant%20might%20have%20earned%20as%20a%20way%20to%20hire%20for%20skills%2C%20not%20a%20college%20degree%2C%20Forsa%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20firm%20Gartner%20reported%20in%20July%20that%2074%25%20of%20HR%20leaders%20it%20surveyed%20believe%20that%20most%20employers%20are%20shifting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gartner.com%2Fen%2Fdocuments%2F5618392%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efocus%20of%20how%20they%20manage%20talent%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20skills.%20Yet%20only%20about%20four%20in%2010%20surveyed%20reported%20that%20their%20organizations%20had%20implemented%20processes%20that%20would%20enable%20this%20to%20play%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFocusing%20on%20skills%20can%20also%20be%20a%20way%20to%20keep%20people%20within%20an%20organization%2C%20not%20just%20hire%20them%2C%20according%20to%20Jon%20Lester%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20HR%20technology%2C%20data%2C%20and%20AI%20at%20IBM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20BI%20that%20nearly%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20the%20average%20IBMer%20spent%2031%20hours%20a%20year%20learning%20new%20skills.%20By%202023%2C%20that%20was%20up%20to%2087%20hours.%20All%20of%20this%20learning%2C%20Lester%20said%2C%20assists%20with%20retention.%20It%20also%20sits%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20how%20IBM%20compensates%20its%20employees%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20get%20salary%20increases%20mostly%20because%20of%20the%20skills%20they've%20learned%2C%26quot%3B%20Lester%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20supports%20that%20thinking.%20According%20to%20McKinsey%2C%20skills%20learned%20at%20work%20contribute%2046%25%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2F~%2Fmedia%2Fmckinsey%2Fbusiness%2520functions%2Fpeople%2520and%2520organizational%2520performance%2Four%2520insights%2Fthe%2520state%2520of%2520organizations%25202023%2Fthe-state-of-organizations-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20person's%20lifetime%20earnings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20her%20part%2C%20as%20McMillan%20continues%20to%20search%20for%20a%20job%2C%20she%20often%20breaks%20down%20in%20tears%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20several%20times%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she's%20been%20filling%20out%20surveys%20and%20doing%20whatever%20else%20she%20can%20to%20earn%20a%20few%20extra%20dollars.%20Last%20month%2C%20a%20friend%20gave%20her%20a%20%2450%20grocery%20store%20gift%20card%20to%20help%20her%20get%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20McMillan%20looks%20at%20job%20listings%20and%20contemplates%20whether%20a%20degree%20is%20necessary%2C%20she%20said%20she%20thinks%20that%20even%20if%20she%20had%20a%20bachelor's%2C%20it%20would%20have%20%26quot%3Bdust%20on%20it%20by%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20would%20have%20had%20to%20evolve%20by%20now%20if%20I%20did%20get%2