nancial%20gift.%20The%20lowest%20donation%20I've%20seen%20is%20%2425%3B%20the%20highest%20is%20%24500.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20think%20it's%20all%20unnecessary%20and%20ridiculous%2C%20and%20I%20certainly%20don't%20want%20to%20donate%20any%20money%20myself.%20I%20understand%20her%20family%20is%20still%20having%20a%20hard%20time%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20not%20a%20significant%20financial%20loss%2C%20but%20this%20woman%20has%20hurt%20people%20I%20love.%20I'm%20not%20interested%20in%20writing%20her%20a%20check%20as%20some%20kind%20of%20gesture%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20want%20the%20drama%20of%20explaining%20myself%20to%20my%20other%20coworkers%2C%20either.%20What%20should%20I%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESincerely%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EColleague%20to%20the%20Conniving%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20Colleague%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoworker%20conflicts%20are%20some%20of%20the%20hardest%20to%20manage%20because%20we%20can't%20avoid%20them.%20We%20don't%20just%20have%20to%20see%20this%20person%20every%20day%3B%20we%20must%20also%20continue%20working%20with%20someone%20we%20already%20know%20isn't%20a%20great%20personal%20match.%20Whether%20it's%20one%20too%20many%20%26quot%3Bper%20my%20last%20emails%26quot%3B%20or%20constant%20snotty%20comments%20during%20meetings%2C%20you're%20still%20expected%20to%20pursue%20the%20same%20goals%20together%20as%20a%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20your%20case%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20your%20issue%20with%20your%20colleague%20goes%20beyond%20a%20few%20snide%20email%20exchanges%3B%20it%20has%20less%20to%20do%20with%20how%20this%20woman%20has%20treated%20you%20and%20more%20to%20do%20with%20how%20she's%20treated%20people%20you%20love.%20This%20makes%20your%20feelings%20toward%20your%20coworker%20harder%20to%20navigate%20because%20it%20goes%20beyond%20irritation%20or%20even%20personal%20hurt%20%E2%80%94%20her%20behavior%20has%20sparked%20your%20loyalty%2C%20your%20sense%20of%20justice%2C%20and%20your%20protective%20instincts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20not%20here%20to%20tell%20you%20what%20to%20do%3B%20as%20long%20as%20you%20move%20with%20civility%20and%20professionalism%2C%20I%20don't%20foresee%20the%20stakes%20being%20incredibly%20high%20whether%20you%20chip%20in%20on%20the%20group%20gift%20or%20not.%20However%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20worth%20asking%20yourself%20what%20you%20hope%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20situation%20in%20either%20case.%20To%20do%20this%2C%20I%20want%20to%20outline%20your%20three%20options%20and%20what%20the%20best%20and%20worst%20outcomes%20might%20be%20with%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20you%20chip%20in%20a%20small%20amount%20%E2%80%94%20%2410%20should%20cover%20it.%20You%20mentioned%20the%20smallest%20donation%20you%20saw%20so%20far%20being%20%2425%3B%20this%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20can't%20set%20a%20new%20record.%20To%20your%20point%2C%20your%20arch-enemy%20was%20smart%20enough%20to%20buy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhomeowners-insurance%2Fbest-homeowners-insurance-companies%5C%22%3Ehomeowners%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20the%20money%20isn't%20about%20her%20needs.%20So%2C%20I%20doubt%20you'll%20be%20judged%20for%20giving%20a%20small%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20other%20coworkers%20simply%20want%20to%20help.%20When%20bad%20things%20happen%20to%20people%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20know%20what%20to%20do%2C%20but%20the%20instinct%20to%20help%20is%20strong%2C%20so%20we%20find%20ways%20to%20support%20them%20anyway.%20This%20often%20means%20giving%20money%20to%20the%20person%20struggling%20%E2%80%94%20who%20couldn't%20use%20a%20few%20more%20dollars%3F%20In%20other%20words%2C%20as%20you%20said%2C%20this%20financial%20offering%20from%20your%20coworkers%20is%20simply%20a%20gesture.%20The%20question%20is%20whether%20you%20will%20participate%20in%20this%20gesture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20go%20this%20route%2C%20worst%20case%2C%20you're%20out%20%2410%2C%20and%20your%20arch-enemy%20has%20the%20satisfaction%20of%20knowing%20that%20you%20went%20along%20with%20the%20crowd%2C%20and%20now%20they%20believe%20they%20can%20prey%20upon%20your%20kindness.%20But%20you%20know%20they%20can't%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20matters.%20In%20the%20best%20case%2C%20you%20spend%20%2410%20and%20never%20have%20to%20think%20about%20it%20again.%20This%20feels%20like%20the%20most%20likely%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%2C%20you%20could%20choose%20your%20second%20option%3A%20Don't%20chip%20in%20and%20let%20everyone%20who%20asks%20know%20why.%20Best%20case%2C%20you%20get%20the%20satisfaction%20of%20knowing%20you%20stood%20firm%20in%20your%20convictions%2C%20and%20you'll%20find%20more%20colleagues%20who%20see%20through%20this%20woman's%20facade%2C%20and%20together%2C%20you%20can%20bring%20the%20truth%20of%20her%20behavior%20to%20light.%20Worst%20(and%20more%20likely)%20case%2C%20you%20will%20cause%20a%20massive%20drama%20ending%20with%20all%20your%20colleagues%20seeing%20you%20as%20an%20angry%2C%20unforgiving%2C%20problem%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20third%20option%20is%20not%20to%20donate%20a%20dime%20and%20hope%20no%20one%20notices.%20Best%20case%2C%20they%20won't.%20In%20the%20worst%20case%2C%20they%20will%20comment%20on%20it.%20I%20find%20the%20best%20case%20more%20likely%2C%20but%20who%20knows%3F%20Either%20way%2C%20the%20stakes%20are%20low.%20So%20low%2C%20I%20wonder%20if%20there%20isn't%20something%20bigger%20behind%20your%20stress%20over%20this%20particular%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20almost%20seems%20like%20you%20want%20the%20stakes%20to%20be%20higher.%20You%20mentioned%20that%20this%20coworker%20is%20%26quot%3Bunderhanded%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpassive-aggressive.%26quot%3B%20These%20types%20of%20behaviors%20can%20be%20especially%20infuriating%20because%20it%20often%20feels%20like%20no%20one%20else%20notices%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20there's%20never%20any%20accountability.%20So%2C%20we%20try%20to%20blow%20up%20small%20things%20to%20finally%20start%20